<subSubSection pageId="55" pageNumber="56" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="55.[151,1437,290,1036]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Morphology. D VI + I,14–16; A I,13–15; P 18. Medium-sized goby with moderately elongate body, large head, snout moderately steep and shorter than eye diameter. Body often held slightly arched. Caudal peduncle deep, but lower than body depth. Dorsal fins of similar height, first dorsal fin may be slightly higher, with more or less rounded margin and no elongate spines. Caudal fin rounded. Scales present on body and on predorsal area, usually visible on photographs on body.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="55.[151,1437,290,1036]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
Live coloration. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[387,1323,505,532]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Body light gray or whitish, usually with blue or yellow reflections on the back</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1339,1424,506,532]" captionStart="FIGURE 39" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1939,1963]" captionTargetBox="[176,1411,1093,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-76@36.[176,1411,1093,1916]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 39. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Gobius fallax. B) Upper lip with brown mark in addition to the dot on the corner of the mouth; dark curved mark on the upper border of the eye connects longitudinally other marks. Photo by R. Pillon, Hvar Island, Croatia, Central Adriatic Sea." pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
). Yellow hues sometimes more visible on the head. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Head and body covered with longitudinal lines of well-defined brown or dark brown dots, those along midline slightly paler</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[925,1013,578,604]" captionStart="FIGURE 39" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1939,1963]" captionTargetBox="[176,1411,1093,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-76@36.[176,1411,1093,1916]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 39. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Gobius fallax. B) Upper lip with brown mark in addition to the dot on the corner of the mouth; dark curved mark on the upper border of the eye connects longitudinally other marks. Photo by R. Pillon, Hvar Island, Croatia, Central Adriatic Sea." pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
). Dots are broadest along the lateral midline but always remain separated. The eyes have brown stripes radiating from the pupil to the orbital rim, 2 of them forming a broad horizontal stripe across the pupil. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Dark curved mark on the upper iris on the eye connects longitudinally other marks</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[494,596,686,713]" captionStart="FIGURE 39" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1939,1963]" captionTargetBox="[176,1411,1093,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-76@36.[176,1411,1093,1916]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 39. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Gobius fallax. B) Upper lip with brown mark in addition to the dot on the corner of the mouth; dark curved mark on the upper border of the eye connects longitudinally other marks. Photo by R. Pillon, Hvar Island, Croatia, Central Adriatic Sea." pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 39b</figureCitation>
). Lower lip with a median W-shaped mark. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">A well-defined dark dot on posterior angle of mouth</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[460,559,722,749]" captionStart="FIGURE 39" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1939,1963]" captionTargetBox="[176,1411,1093,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-76@36.[176,1411,1093,1916]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 39. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Gobius fallax. B) Upper lip with brown mark in addition to the dot on the corner of the mouth; dark curved mark on the upper border of the eye connects longitudinally other marks. Photo by R. Pillon, Hvar Island, Croatia, Central Adriatic Sea." pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 39b</figureCitation>
). Upper lip with brown marks in addition to the dot on the corner of the mouth (
<figureCitation box="[160,258,758,785]" captionStart="FIGURE 39" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1939,1963]" captionTargetBox="[176,1411,1093,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-76@36.[176,1411,1093,1916]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 39. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Gobius fallax. B) Upper lip with brown mark in addition to the dot on the corner of the mouth; dark curved mark on the upper border of the eye connects longitudinally other marks. Photo by R. Pillon, Hvar Island, Croatia, Central Adriatic Sea." pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 39b</figureCitation>
). Snout with M-shaped line and an oblique preorbital bar (Herler 
<emphasis box="[993,1042,758,784]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">et al</emphasis>
. 2005; 
<bibRefCitation author="Renoult, J. P. &amp; Pillon, R. &amp; Kovacic, M. &amp; Louisy, P." box="[1126,1346,758,784]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refId="ref63723" refString="Renoult, J. P., Pillon, R., Kovacic, M. &amp; Louisy, P. (2022) Frontiers in Fishwatching Series - Gobies of North-eastern Atlantic and the Mediterranean: Gobius and Thorogobius. Les cahiers de la fondation Biotope. [in press]" type="book" year="2022">
Renoult 
<emphasis box="[1222,1271,758,784]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">et al</emphasis>
. 2022
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
