<paragraph blockId="55.[151,1437,290,1036]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
Habitat. Infralittoral species, known from 
<quantity box="[668,752,830,856]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.65" metricValueMax="3.2" metricValueMin="0.1" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" unit="m" value="16.5" valueMax="32.0" valueMin="1.0">1–32 m</quantity>
depth on mixed sandy-rocky habitats, rock crevices or stones nearby soft bottom, sometimes covered with seagrass (Herler &amp; Patzner 2005; 
<bibRefCitation author="Louisy, P." box="[1035,1180,866,893]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refId="ref60639" refString="Louisy, P. (2015) Europe and Mediterranean Marine Fish Identification Guide. 3 rd Edition. Eugen Ulmer Ed., Paris, 512 pp." type="book" year="2015">Louisy 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="55.[151,1437,290,1036]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
Geographic distribution. Mediterranean. Recorded from many places from the Balearic Islands to 
<collectingCountry box="[1271,1351,902,928]" name="Turkey" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fricke, R. &amp; Musa Sari, H." pageId="55" pageNumber="56" pagination="1 - 169" refId="ref54778" refString="Fricke, R., Bilecenog ˘ lu, M. &amp; Musa Sari, H. (2007) Annotated checklist of fish and lamprey species (Gnathostomata and Petromyzontomorphi) of Turkey, including a Red List of threatened and declining species. Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde, Serie A (Biologie), 706, 1 - 169." type="journal article" year="2007">
Fricke 
<emphasis box="[151,201,938,964]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">et al</emphasis>
. 2007
</bibRefCitation>
), including 
<collectingCountry box="[409,491,938,964]" name="Croatia" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Croatia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Patzner, R. A." box="[507,790,938,964]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" pagination="177 - 206" refId="ref58470" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Patzner, R. A. (2011) North-Eastern Atlantic and Mediterranean Gobies. In: Patzner, R. A., Van Tassell, J. L., Kovacic, M. &amp; Kapoor, B. G. (Eds.), The Biology of Gobies. Science Publishers, Jersey, British Isles, pp. 177 - 206. https: // doi. org / 10.1201 / b 11397" type="book chapter" year="2011">Kovačić &amp; Patzner 2011</bibRefCitation>
), Crete (Kovačić 
<emphasis box="[988,1038,938,964]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">et al</emphasis>
. 2011), 
<collectingCountry box="[1132,1213,938,964]" name="Cyprus" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Cyprus</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Golani, D." pageId="55" pageNumber="56" pagination="89 - 91" refId="ref58212" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Golani, D. (2007 a) First record of three gobiid species in the Levant. Cybium, 31 (1), 89 - 91. https: // doi. org / 10.26028 / cybium / 2007 - 311 - 013" type="journal article" year="2007">Kovačić &amp; Golani 2007a</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[284,349,974,1000]" name="Libya" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Libya</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Al-Hassan, L. A. J. &amp; El-Silini, O." box="[364,683,974,1000]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" pagination="291 - 301" refId="ref50837" refString="Al-Hassan, L. A. J. &amp; El-Silini, O. A (1999) Check-list of bony fishes collected from the Mediterranean coast of Benghazi, Libya. Revista de Biologia Marina y Oceanografia, 34, 291 - 301." type="journal article" year="1999">Al-Hassan &amp; El-Silini 1999</bibRefCitation>
). Also recorded in Gran Canaria, Atlantic (
<bibRefCitation author="Dooley, J. K. &amp; Van Tassell, J. V. &amp; Brito A." box="[1165,1380,974,1001]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" pagination="1 - 49" refId="ref53046" refString="Dooley, J. K., Van Tassell, J. V. &amp; Brito A. (1985) An annotated check-list of the fishes of the Canary Islands. American Museum Novitates, 2824, 1 - 49." type="journal article" year="1985">
Dooley 
<emphasis box="[1257,1306,974,1000]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">et al</emphasis>
. 1985
</bibRefCitation>
), but this needs to be confirmed because of taxonomic progress on the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Risso" authorityYear="1810" box="[883,1057,1010,1036]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Gobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="auratus">
<emphasis box="[883,1057,1010,1036]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Gobius auratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex since this record.
</paragraph>
